xml:lang="en"><q>my granary is full of bread, my ground is abundant</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>15</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Из <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>barakat</w><gloss><q>изобилие</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w/><gloss><q>благоденствие</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><w/><gloss><q>довольство</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>barakad</w></mentioned>. Распространено по всему Кавказу: <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>berakat</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w>bierkat</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/><w>barkàt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lbe"><lang/><w>baračat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>bereket</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w>baraket</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>baraka</w></mentioned>. В осетинский это слово было заимствовано дважды: сперва в форме %ibærkad%i (через дагестанское посредство, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/><w>barkàt</w></mentioned>), позднее в форме <xr><ref target="#entry_bæræḱet"/></xr> | %ibereket%i (через кабардинское посредство, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/><w>baraket</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><w>bereket</w></mentioned>, ). Ср. другие случаи двукратного заимствования одного и того же слова: <xr><ref target="#entry_ærx"/></xr> и <xr><ref target="#entry_aryq"/><ref target="#entry_lawyz"/></xr> и <xr><ref target="#entry_kʼælæt"/><ref target="#entry_lwasi"/></xr> и <xr><ref target="#entry_kʼalati"/></xr>.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>93</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>barakat</w><gloss><q>abundance</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w/><gloss><q>welfare</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><w/><gloss><q>contentment</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>barakad</w></mentioned>. The word is widespread all over the Caucasus: <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>berakat</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w>bierkat</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/><w>barkàt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lbe"><lang/><w>baračat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>bereket</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w>baraket</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>baraka</w></mentioned>. The word was borrowed in Ossetic twice: firstly, in the form %ibærkad%i (through Dagestan, cf. <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/><w>barkàt</w></mentioned>), later in the form <xr><ref target="#entry_bæræḱet"/></xr> | %ibereket%i (through Kabardian, cf. <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/><w>baraket</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><w>bereket</w></mentioned>, ). Cf. other cases of double borrowing of the same word: <xr><ref target="#entry_ærx"/></xr> and <xr><ref target="#entry_aryq"/><ref target="#entry_lawyz"/></xr> and <xr><ref target="#entry_kʼælæt"/><ref target="#entry_lwasi"/></xr> and <xr><ref target="#entry_kʼalati"/></xr>.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>93</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>